name: NEXTA
description:
May 23, 2021. A plane of Ryanair
air-company was flying from Athens
to Vilnius over Belarus, where it was
turned due to false reports of
explosion hazard, and forced to land
in Minsk. After landing, Roman
Protasevich, co-founder of the
Belarusian opposition telegram
channel NEXTA, who is wanted by the
Belarusian authorities, was detained
and dropped off the plane. Now he
faces up to 15 years in prison.
